@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{color-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in @code{color} library with
practical tools for working with color values in everyday editing.
Theme authors, CSS developers, and anyone who manipulates color codes
in source files will find it useful.

The package provides three main capabilities:

@itemize
@item
@strong{Conversion} between hexadecimal (HEX) and Hue-Saturation-Luminance
(HSL) color representations, either for the color at point or for
every color in a buffer (@ref{Conversion, , Conversion commands}).
@item
@strong{Contrast analysis} against white, black, and an optional reference
color, following the WCAG contrast ratio standard
(@ref{Contrast analysis}).
@item
@strong{Embark integration} that lets you act on any HEX or HSL color
string with a single keystroke (@ref{Embark integration}).
@end itemize

Internally, the package relies on Emacs' built-in @code{color-rgb-to-hsl}
and @code{color-hsl-to-rgb} for the mathematical conversions and on the
@samp{ct} package for contrast ratio computation.

