@chapter Variables

@menu
* Regular expression patterns::
@end menu

@node Regular expression patterns
@section Regular expression patterns

@vindex color-extras-hex-pattern
The constant @code{color-extras-hex-pattern} is a regular expression that
matches a six-digit hexadecimal RGB color string, with or without a
leading @samp{#}.  The first capture group contains the six hex digits.
This pattern is used throughout the package to detect HEX colors at
point and in buffer-wide searches (@ref{Conversion, , Conversion commands}).

@vindex color-extras-hsl-scaled-pattern
The constant @code{color-extras-hsl-scaled-pattern} is a regular expression
that matches an HSL color written as three comma-separated numbers
(e.g., @samp{210, 50%, 40%}).  Hue ranges from 0 to 360; saturation and
luminance range from 0 to 100 and may include trailing @samp{%}  signs.
The three capture groups correspond to hue, saturation, and luminance.

